WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:01.920
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.920 --> 00:00:03.227
Praise the Lord.

00:00:03.227 --> 00:00:06.629
Easter weekend, my favorite time of the year.

00:00:06.629 --> 00:00:08.343
Well, praise the Lord, I'm excited.

00:00:08.343 --> 00:00:09.657
It's time to be grateful.

00:00:09.657 --> 00:00:15.573
It's time to be thankful for all that Jesus has done for every single one of us.

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:17.387
It's a time to reflect.

00:00:18.267 --> 00:00:36.819
I always just sit and watch my kids and the church things that we go to, and it makes me go inward and think about all that Jesus did—all his suffering, all that he did to break the chains of bondage off of our lives so that we could walk free.

00:00:41.343 --> 00:00:43.920
You know, I bring out this video.

00:00:44.180 --> 00:00:51.520
I've brought out a lot of videos the last couple of days that I've already brought out before, and I usually do it once a year.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:01:00.829
These are the experiences that I've had with the Lord that have changed me, and they're too good just to let get buried in the algorithm.

00:01:00.829 --> 00:01:04.360
They get weighed down at the bottom of the feed and people forget about them.

00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:22.370
So Braden, Diana, and I bring those videos out again because we believe there's life still in those videos, in that experience that I had with the Lord—that word that the Lord gave to tell you all about his coming and where the tribulation was.

00:01:22.370 --> 00:01:26.034
And now this one is about his crucifixion.

00:01:26.034 --> 00:01:36.514
I was sitting on the side of my bed one night and I was asking the Lord because one of the people of the church called and said, "Brandon, I've been suffering with arthritis for years.

00:01:36.514 --> 00:01:38.300
My hands are crippled up.

00:01:38.300 --> 00:01:39.849
I can't move my hands.

00:01:39.849 --> 00:01:41.760
I've been in so much pain.

00:01:41.760 --> 00:01:43.880
How come you think I've been a preacher?

00:01:43.880 --> 00:01:48.175
" He told me all the things that he had done and how he's still suffering.

00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:50.606
And so I thought, "I don't know.

00:01:51.702 --> 00:01:53.213
I'm overcoming stuff myself.

00:01:53.213 --> 00:01:56.429
My daughter's overcoming, and I've been standing in faith.

00:01:56.429 --> 00:02:08.448
" And I told him all my sob story, you know, after you tell your sob stories of everything you go through and you listen to each other, but it still didn't fix the problem because you still are overcoming what you're overcoming.

00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:18.044
So I sat on the side of the bed and I said, "Lord, would you please explain to me why all the body of Christ is not healed?

00:02:18.044 --> 00:02:20.286
Why are we not experiencing the glory?

00:02:20.286 --> 00:02:26.680
Why have we not seen the manifestation of what we're believing for?

00:02:26.680 --> 00:02:36.420
" So I just went to sleep and all of a sudden, in that sleeping time, I had a dream.

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:44.320
Now you know when you have a dream that is just an over-the-top dream, where you can smell things?

00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:47.408
This was like I was out of my body in my dream.

00:02:47.408 --> 00:02:52.500
This was such a supernatural dream that it was real.

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:55.771
All of a sudden, I was standing in this courtyard.

00:02:55.771 --> 00:02:59.267
It was hot outside, probably about 80 degrees.

00:02:59.267 --> 00:03:00.693
I could actually feel the temperature.

00:03:00.693 --> 00:03:02.639
I could feel the sun hitting me.

00:03:02.639 --> 00:03:05.440
You know, whenever you're standing out there and there's no breeze?

00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:08.040
In the dream, I could feel how hot it was.

00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:13.497
And I looked around me and all of a sudden to my right hand, Jesus was standing there.

00:03:13.497 --> 00:03:16.480
And then I realized where I was.

00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:22.539
I was taken back in time and I was at the crucifixion because I could see Jesus.

00:03:23.899 --> 00:03:28.080
The Jesus that I was seeing had oily skin.

00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:31.407
He had his shirt off.

00:03:31.407 --> 00:03:33.428
His skin was dirty looking.

00:03:33.428 --> 00:03:40.075
He looked like he had dirt on him and he was being led to the whipping post.

00:03:40.945 --> 00:03:50.160
They took his hands, ladies and gentlemen, and they put them in shackles and they tied him to a whipping post in front of my face.

00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:59.062
And I could see the stanchion right here with this metal-looking hoop.

00:03:59.062 --> 00:04:04.640
And they put his hands and latched his hands on that hoop-looking thing.

00:04:04.640 --> 00:04:07.058
They put his hands up there like that.

00:04:07.058 --> 00:04:12.639
And there was a man that was dressed in solid black over on his right hand.

00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:16.240
He was probably about 300 pounds.

00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:21.089
He was a big guy, bigger than me.

00:04:21.089 --> 00:04:25.040
This man was big, and his body structure was big.

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:28.880
His shoulders were big, but he was bald-headed with a shaved head.

00:04:30.302 --> 00:04:33.059
And on his left side was a man in Roman garb.

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:44.480
He had a Roman helmet on, a Roman outfit on—the leather-looking outfit.

00:04:48.436 --> 00:04:53.520
It was all just like you see in Roman times.

00:04:55.760 --> 00:04:59.480
Both men had the cat-o'-nine-tails in their hands.

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:02.844
And I saw the one man take...

00:05:02.844 --> 00:05:05.973
well, first I saw them pull his beard.

00:05:05.973 --> 00:05:08.057
I saw them rip out his beard.

00:05:08.057 --> 00:05:11.499
They were punching Jesus in the face.

00:05:11.499 --> 00:05:17.547
I could see Jesus's head bounce around as they were just beating him in the face and punching him.

00:05:17.547 --> 00:05:20.020
They were ripping his beard out of his face.

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:26.159
They were pushing on the crown of thorns on his head because he had a crown of thorns on his head as he was there.

00:05:27.439 --> 00:05:30.770
His skin looked like it had been welped up.

00:05:30.770 --> 00:05:38.889
He looked like he had been beaten, and his back already looked bruised from somebody beating on him.

00:05:39.299 --> 00:05:48.514
His body already looked like it was—you know, whenever you see skin that was already like you were beaten with sticks?

00:05:56.009 --> 00:05:56.311
He looked like he had purple burst blood vessels that were already popped all over his back.

00:05:56.311 --> 00:06:06.899
He looked like someone who had been in a bad fight and had lost, totally purple from his body being beaten through his olive skin.

00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:15.729
And you could see the glistening on his back that looked like oil from the sweat from how hot it was outside.

00:06:15.729 --> 00:06:22.280
It was about 80 or 85 degrees, but you could see the oils from his skin.

00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:31.050
And I just remember looking at his body and I saw him being lifted up like this, above his head.

00:06:31.050 --> 00:06:41.623
And I saw his bruises all over his body and his face, and he had blood from where the beard was being ripped out of his face.

00:06:41.623 --> 00:06:49.680
There was blood dripping and it looked like what you would look like if you had hair ripped out of your head.

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:51.840
And I could see the thorns, like I said.

00:06:51.840 --> 00:07:01.626
So these men were taking the thorns and they were pushing them on his head more because they had things on their hands, so it wasn't hurting them, but it was hurting Jesus.

00:07:01.626 --> 00:07:09.830
And I could see he was in tremendous pain.

00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:24.338
As I stood there with Jesus on this side in his glorified body, I could see him and he was watching on, and we were looking at him being whipped.

00:07:24.338 --> 00:07:34.097
And I saw the one man in the black outfit take that cat-o'-nine-tails and he went and he whipped him.

00:07:34.097 --> 00:07:40.819
And whenever he did, I saw flesh stripped off of his body like it was just big chunks.

00:07:40.819 --> 00:07:43.376
It was not just like a little bitty scratch.

00:07:43.376 --> 00:07:50.345
Ladies and gentlemen, what I saw before me was horrific.

00:07:50.345 --> 00:07:56.705
And all that came off of his body and it just scratched him deep to the bones.

00:07:56.705 --> 00:08:02.738
Then they took the other man and he took that other side and they whipped him again on this side.

00:08:02.738 --> 00:08:05.096
And as one was whipping this side, the other...

00:08:05.348 --> 00:08:07.970
and they would take turns, and each one would whip.

00:08:09.004 --> 00:08:10.434
It wasn't a break.

00:08:10.434 --> 00:08:17.627
One would whip, then the other, to the point where his flesh was dripping off of his body.

00:08:18.667 --> 00:08:23.449
Every time he was being hit, it was like he was being moved and he was screaming in agony.

00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:37.534
All I could do while I was standing there was say, "Stop!

00:08:37.534 --> 00:08:39.034
You've got to stop!

00:08:39.034 --> 00:08:40.819
" but nobody could hear me.

00:08:40.819 --> 00:08:43.460
I said, "Oh, God, they've got to stop!

00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:48.434
" because I could see his body in the pain that he was feeling.

00:08:48.434 --> 00:09:13.590
Because his arms were above his head, it was going around his chest and it was taking his skin off of his body in chunks—not just a little bit, but deep, deep wounds were just being lashed and scraped and ripped out of his body as he was taking all of the stripes for us.

00:09:13.600 --> 00:09:18.560
Blood was dripping down him and he was just in a pool of blood all around him.

00:09:18.560 --> 00:09:31.271
And Jesus said this to me: "What part of 'By my stripes you are healed' do you not understand?

00:09:31.271 --> 00:09:33.285
" He was pointing at himself.

00:09:33.285 --> 00:09:36.880
He said, "I took all that on the cross for you.

00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:40.479
I took all sickness, all disease, everything for you.

00:09:40.479 --> 00:09:47.865
And I said in my word, 'By my stripes you are healed.

00:09:47.865 --> 00:09:53.219
'" He said, "Brandon, I want to tell you something.

00:09:55.613 --> 00:10:06.000
The same way you believe that you're saved is the same way you believe for your healing.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:12.547
" He said, "Brandon, if anybody was to tell you that you were not saved, you would fight them, wouldn't you?

00:10:12.547 --> 00:10:14.420
You would say, 'Oh, I know I'm saved.

00:10:14.420 --> 00:10:17.733
You know it,' because you're that convinced in your heart.

00:10:17.733 --> 00:10:25.635
But yet, you have nothing to assure you other than your faith that you are.

00:10:25.635 --> 00:10:35.400
You have no way of believing other than by what you've heard me say, or the preacher say, that you are saved by grace through faith.

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:45.691
And you believed and you received it and you just latched on to it, but you're convinced, no matter if you sin or whatever, that you believe that you're saved.

00:10:45.691 --> 00:10:47.496
" I said, "That's right.

00:10:47.496 --> 00:10:52.068
" And he said, "And if they would tell you you weren't saved, you would fight them.

00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:55.470
You would argue with them and say, 'No, I know I'm saved.

00:10:55.470 --> 00:10:57.269
' They say, 'No, I don't believe you're saved.

00:10:57.269 --> 00:10:58.180
' 'No, I know I'm saved.

00:10:58.180 --> 00:10:59.893
You're not going to tell me I'm not saved.

00:10:59.893 --> 00:11:09.714
'" I said, "That's exactly right," because I could see myself in this experience saying that as somebody was telling me, "I don't believe you're saved.

00:11:09.714 --> 00:11:11.279
" I said, "Well, I know I'm saved.

00:11:11.279 --> 00:11:12.453
I know I'm saved.

00:11:12.453 --> 00:11:14.937
" And I was fully persuaded that I know I'm saved.

00:11:14.937 --> 00:11:20.720
But yet, I had no outward appearance, because I know when I fall and I mess up every day, somebody does.

00:11:20.720 --> 00:11:27.760
But yet, I'm still convinced that Jesus Christ forgave me of my sins and my name is written in the Lamb's Book of Life.

00:11:27.760 --> 00:11:34.465
He said, "Healing and salvation are the same.

00:11:34.465 --> 00:11:37.975
By my stripes, you are healed.

00:11:37.975 --> 00:11:42.818
I took it on the cross for you, just like I took your sin on the cross.

00:11:42.818 --> 00:11:43.965
I took your poverty.

00:11:43.965 --> 00:11:46.346
I became poor that you might be rich.

00:11:46.346 --> 00:11:51.206
I took it all for you, just like I did salvation.

00:11:51.206 --> 00:11:57.016
But yet you believe in the salvation more than what you believe in the healing.

00:11:57.016 --> 00:12:06.635
When you believe the same way you believe for your salvation, then nobody can talk you out of it.

00:12:06.635 --> 00:12:08.994
It's the same way you believe for your healing.

00:12:08.994 --> 00:12:15.206
" He said, "When you believe it the same way, Brandon, that's where your manifestation comes.

00:12:15.206 --> 00:12:27.507
Believing it whenever you don't see it, believing it when you still feel the symptom of what you're going through.

00:12:27.507 --> 00:12:35.645
" He said, "When you believe it, that I took all of it on the cross for you.

00:12:35.645 --> 00:12:43.047
I became that for you: sickness, disease, poverty, lack, mental anguish.

00:12:43.047 --> 00:12:57.450
" From the crown of thorns, what he went through in the Garden of Gethsemane praying, the blood was coming from him from the pressure of what he was about to do.

00:12:57.450 --> 00:13:09.829
He sweat great drops of blood out of his skin because of the pressure, the mental torment of realizing what he was about to go through.

00:13:09.839 --> 00:13:17.691
Jesus paid the ultimate price today on this beautiful Easter Sunday.

00:13:17.691 --> 00:13:23.947
Never take it for granted what Jesus did for you.

00:13:23.947 --> 00:13:25.813
I saw his pain.

00:13:25.813 --> 00:13:32.240
I saw his suffering, and it was more than what anybody can comprehend.

00:13:32.240 --> 00:13:49.680
I don't know why Jesus chose to show me what he went through.

00:13:49.680 --> 00:14:16.862
When I saw the pain that he went through, just that part of it—not even them taking him out and making him carry his cross with all his flesh hanging off his body and all the loss of blood, and then driving those huge nails in his hands and his feet, then shoving that spear in his side and blood and water flowed.

00:14:16.862 --> 00:14:20.900
And then he said, "It is finished.

00:14:20.900 --> 00:14:21.440
" It is finished.

00:14:22.520 --> 00:14:25.519
What was finished, ladies and gentlemen?

00:14:25.519 --> 00:14:30.906
Everything he set out to do to set you free, it is finished.

00:14:30.906 --> 00:14:32.613
"I did it all.

00:14:32.613 --> 00:14:35.251
I paid the price.

00:14:35.251 --> 00:14:42.004
" A sinless Lamb for the whole world.

00:14:42.004 --> 00:14:44.657
His blood was shed for you.

00:14:44.657 --> 00:14:47.743
Not one of you deserves it.

00:14:47.743 --> 00:14:49.599
Not one of us can earn it.

00:14:49.599 --> 00:14:58.640
But all of us can come to him by grace through faith and say, "Jesus, I believe what you did for me today.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:02.686
" Today on this Easter, it's not about Easter eggs.

00:15:02.686 --> 00:15:04.300
It's not about Easter candy.

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:08.480
It's not about a good meal after Easter service.

00:15:08.480 --> 00:15:15.680
It's not about going out with family and friends and having a picnic or whatever you all want to do.

00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:17.600
It's about what he paid the price for.

00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:31.451
Yes, we celebrate it and we're thankful, but it's really a time of inward reflection to say, "Is my all on the altar?

00:15:31.451 --> 00:15:37.813
Have I truly made Jesus Christ the Lord and my personal savior?

00:15:37.813 --> 00:15:39.787
Am I sold out?

00:15:39.787 --> 00:15:44.480
Do I realize that he's coming back again?

00:15:44.480 --> 00:15:49.964
Am I suffering with something that I don't need to have in my body anymore?

00:15:49.964 --> 00:15:57.013
Am I dealing with some kind of perversion in my life that I think that I have to, whenever Jesus paid the price?

00:15:57.013 --> 00:16:02.800
" In Galatians, it says, "Christ has redeemed me from the curse of the law.

00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:06.000
" Jesus paid the price for every single one of you.

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:12.320
And that's why I take communion daily, because this represents his body that was broken.

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:18.000
This represents his blood that was dripped all over, and he became sickness.

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:19.590
He became death.

00:16:19.590 --> 00:16:23.360
He became all that he did on the cross.

00:16:23.547 --> 00:16:24.605
This is what it represents.

00:16:24.605 --> 00:16:32.040
And now he dwells on the inside of me because I confessed him as my Lord and Savior.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:38.560
He dwells on the inside of me, and I'm healed by those stripes.

00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:46.274
And when Jesus looked at me and he said, "What more do you need to understand?

00:16:46.274 --> 00:16:51.226
" because I said before, if you remember what I said, I said, "I don't understand it, Lord.

00:16:51.226 --> 00:16:52.897
Can you explain it to me?

00:16:52.897 --> 00:16:55.880
Can you explain to me why people are sick?

00:16:55.880 --> 00:17:01.583
" He looked back at me and he reminded me of what I said before I went to bed.

00:17:01.583 --> 00:17:06.160
He said, "What more do you need to understand?

00:17:06.160 --> 00:17:10.957
By my stripes you are healed.

00:17:10.957 --> 00:17:21.599
I took it all for you, the same way I did for your salvation and the same way I took your poverty.

00:17:21.599 --> 00:17:23.1000
You don't have to be poor.

00:17:23.1000 --> 00:17:25.590
You don't have to be poor in spirit.

00:17:25.590 --> 00:17:27.930
You don't have to be poor in anything.

00:17:27.930 --> 00:17:30.620
I became that so you could be blessed.

00:17:30.620 --> 00:17:36.365
" It was so simple the way he described it to me that even a child can understand that.

00:17:36.365 --> 00:17:37.985
Do you believe it?

00:17:39.520 --> 00:17:49.039
And if you do, do you believe you receive it the same way, that today you have the opportunity to accept Jesus Christ as your Lord and personal savior?

00:17:49.039 --> 00:17:51.623
And you say to me, "Brandon, I don't even know that.

00:17:51.623 --> 00:17:54.827
I've never accepted him as Lord and personal savior.

00:17:54.827 --> 00:17:58.870
" Well, today's your day.

00:17:58.880 --> 00:18:00.672
I want to lead you in a prayer.

00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:03.120
We're going to take communion as believers today.

00:18:03.120 --> 00:18:10.297
And we're going to believe that today's your day, that you don't have to go through sickness and disease anymore.

00:18:10.297 --> 00:18:13.680
You don't have to go through poverty anymore.

00:18:13.680 --> 00:18:25.840
And that those stripes, that suffering, everything he did on that cross 2,000 years plus ago is the day he took it for you, ladies and gentlemen.

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:29.420
And that you don't have to be bound by a devil anymore.

00:18:33.287 --> 00:18:39.619
Jesus paid the price, the ultimate price, his life for you to walk in victory.

00:18:39.619 --> 00:18:42.573
Today's your day to walk in victory.

00:18:42.573 --> 00:18:43.066
Why?

00:18:43.066 --> 00:18:45.039
Because it's already done.

00:18:45.039 --> 00:18:45.499
Why?

00:18:45.499 --> 00:18:47.800
He said, "It is finished.

00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:50.347
" And he gave up his ghost.

00:18:53.651 --> 00:18:58.679
Everything I set out to do to make my people free, I did it.

00:18:59.506 --> 00:19:00.746
I finished the race.

00:19:03.644 --> 00:19:04.887
I fought the good fight for you, Father.

00:19:04.887 --> 00:19:08.400
I finished my race.

00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:10.799
I finished my course.

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:20.799
And it is finished.

00:19:28.160 --> 00:19:30.799
Now you say, "I don't even know the salvation.

00:19:30.799 --> 00:19:32.231
" This is all you've got to say.

00:19:34.986 --> 00:19:35.199
It doesn't have to be religious.

00:19:35.199 --> 00:19:39.325
It just has to be a simple little prayer that you believe in your heart.

00:19:39.325 --> 00:19:47.775
The Bible says, "If you confess your sins, he is faithful and just to forgive you of your sins and cleanse you of all unrighteousness.

00:19:47.775 --> 00:19:49.112
" Today's your day.

00:19:50.989 --> 00:20:03.919
Today is a brand new day to get born again, to give it all to Jesus and to know that, as the old man has passed away, behold, I have made all things new.

00:20:03.919 --> 00:20:05.748
That's what the Bible says.

00:20:05.748 --> 00:20:14.390
As you confess it now, this is all you have to say: "Jesus, I believe you're the son of God.

00:20:14.390 --> 00:20:20.920
I believe that you died on the cross and you rose again on the third day.

00:20:23.631 --> 00:20:31.045
" I believe that you did all that for me, and I want to make you my Lord and personal Savior.

00:20:31.045 --> 00:20:38.174
Jesus, write my name in the Lamb's Book of Life.

00:20:48.320 --> 00:20:48.784
Forgive me of all my sins.

00:20:48.784 --> 00:20:54.400
I'm coming to you, Lord, and I want you to be my Savior.

00:20:55.120 --> 00:21:03.375
I want you to be my Lord.

00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:07.890
I want you to be the captain of my ship.

00:21:07.890 --> 00:21:14.655
Forgive me.

00:21:16.080 --> 00:21:19.720
I need a Savior; I need a friend.

00:21:19.720 --> 00:21:22.460
I need you in my life.

00:21:24.026 --> 00:21:24.302
I need you.

00:21:26.823 --> 00:21:27.051
I can't do this without you anymore.

00:21:27.051 --> 00:21:28.045
Thank you, Lord.

00:21:28.045 --> 00:21:31.840
Thank you, Lord, for what you did for me.

